# Git commits: no Cursor attribution

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any Cursor/Changelog footer to commit messages.
- Do **not** list Cursor as a contributor in commit trailers or GitHub co-author metadata.
- When creating commits in this repo, use **`git commit --no-verify`** only if a local hook incorrectly injects Cursor co-author lines; prefer fixing the hook so normal commits stay valid.

Human authors own authorship; AI assistance must not appear in `git log` or GitHub contributor attribution.

## If commits already contain Cursor trailers

Inspect with `git log -1 --format=%B`. To strip `Co-authored-by: Cursor` from a range of commits without changing code:

`FILTER_BRANCH_SQUELCH_WARNING=1 git filter-branch -f --msg-filter 'sed "/^Co-authored-by: Cursor/d"' HEAD~N..HEAD`

Then `git push --force-with-lease`. Prefer fixing the prepare-commit-msg hook or Cursor Git integration so trailers are never added.

## Cursor IDE

Disable any setting that **automatically adds Cursor as co-author** on commit (e.g. Git / version control settings). Otherwise trailers will reappear even when using `--no-verify`.
